            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Just wanted to stop by and say please don't enable suspend on Windows by default. There's no \"unsuspend\" signal and the process just gets stuck and has to be killed. [I've been caught by this and it's not fun](https://github.com/parkovski/config/blob/ae16204ab3ccce8e427fa591e7f7be6c973923d5/.vimrc#L36).\r\n\r\nEven if you add some sort of unsuspend event, there's no canonical way to do this so it really would need a warning message with instructions on how to undo on the first use.",
