            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "> What is \"this\" exactly? This issue tracks a feature that wasn't implemented.\r\n\r\nIf this feature is not implemented, why does it have a hotkey that basically kills nvim when pressed in Windows?\r\nWhat makes it worse is that Ctrl + Z is the universally accepted shortcut for Undo and it's written into the muscle memory for a lot of people. People keep losing work after accidentally pressing Ctrl + Z and crashing neovim. \r\nIs it possible to at least disable this shortcut by default in Windows?\r\n\r\n**Workaround for people starting to learn vim and struggling with this issue:**\r\n\r\nOpen file: C:\\users\\your_name\\appdata\\local\\nvim\\init.vim\r\nCreate it if it doesn't exist. \r\nPaste the following line into the file:\r\n`noremap <C-Z> u`\r\nSave and quit.\r\nNow Ctrl+Z in normal mode will undo the last operation and won't freeze nvim forever.",
